{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 9, "line_start": 9, "page_hint": null, "section": "Instrumentation And Controls Development For H.C. $3.00; Mn .65", "text": "INSTRUMENTATION AND CONTROLS DEVELOPMENT FOR H.C. $3.00; MN .65"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 101, "line_start": 101, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "The reference design of a molten salt breeder reactor (MSBR) is described in ORNL-3996 (Ref."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 101, "line_start": 101, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "Criteria for a molten salt breeder experiment (MSBE) and a schedule for designing and building that reactor are presented in TM-1851 (Ref."}
{"claim_type": "reactor-physics", "line_end": 101, "line_start": 101, "page_hint": null, "section": "Introduction", "text": "The proposal does not include a discussion of control rods or other means of reactivity control; this is included in TM-1855, Component Development Program."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 130, "line_start": 130, "page_hint": null, "section": "Nuclear Instrument Components and Systems", "text": "All neutron sensors used in the MSRE are in a water-filled penetration whose temperature does not exceed $160^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 138, "line_start": 138, "page_hint": null, "section": "Process Instrument Components for Direct Application to Molten-Salt Loops", "text": "Also, the electrical conductivity of the MSBE salts $^{(1)}$ will have a significant effect on the type of primary sensing elements that can be used on the heated salt systems."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 148, "line_start": 148, "page_hint": null, "section": "Flow Measurement", "text": "Since this instrument has piezo-electric transducers mounted on the transmitter body, it is limited to process temperatures below $500^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ and is probably not suitable for use in high level nuclear radiation environment."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 154, "line_start": 154, "page_hint": null, "section": "Flow Measurement", "text": "A turbine type flowmeter was developed for the ANP program and operated satisfactorily at $1600^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ for a short period before failure."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 156, "line_start": 156, "page_hint": null, "section": "Flow Measurement", "text": "Magnetic flowmeters have been used extensively at high temperatures $(1600^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F})$ in liquid metal system and lower temperatures for measurement of a variety of fluid flows."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 156, "line_start": 156, "page_hint": null, "section": "Flow Measurement", "text": "Containment and material compatibility considerations prevented the use of electrical lead-through penetrations of the meter body such as used in conventional magnetic flowmeter construction and the relatively poor (1 mho/cm) conductivity of the molten-salt prevented measurement of signal voltage at the outside surface of the meter body as is done in liquid metal flowmeters."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 156, "line_start": 156, "page_hint": null, "section": "Flow Measurement", "text": "If the conductivities of MSRE salts were found to be greater than that of the MSRE salt by a factor of 1000 or more, liquid-metal magnetic-flowmeter techniques could be used for measurement of molten-salt flow."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 162, "line_start": 162, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "This type of system is inherently radiation resistant, is not sensitive to the effects of varying ambient pressure, and is relatively insensitive to ambient temperature variations below $150^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 162, "line_start": 162, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "(Performance of similar systems used in the HRE-2 was also acceptable)."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 170, "line_start": 170, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "Also, the $150^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ maximum temperature rating of the pneumatic weigh cells precludes their use in the $1200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ambient expected in the MSBE drain tank cells."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 172, "line_start": 172, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "One weigh system, offered by a Swedish company (ASEA), has considerable promise.[2] The load cell in this system is essentially a misdesigned transformer utilizing the magnetic anisotropy which occurs in a magnetic material under mechanical stress."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 172, "line_start": 172, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "The standard model ASEA load cell is not suitable for extended service in high level radiation or high temperature $(1200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F})$ environments; however, available information indicates that adequate radiation resistance could be obtained by replacement of organic electrical insulation materials with inorganic materials and that the maximum operating temperature might be extended to the point where satisfactory operation could be obtained by air cooling the load cells."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 174, "line_start": 174, "page_hint": null, "section": "Salt Inventory", "text": "Substitution of NaK for oil should permit operation of the primary load cell at $1200^{\\circ}\\mathbf{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 180, "line_start": 180, "page_hint": null, "section": "Temperature Measurement", "text": "Results of developmental tests and observation of field performance of this type of thermocouple indicate that an initial (hot junction) measurement accuracy of $\\pm 2^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ and a long term drift rate of less than $2^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ /year can be obtained at operating temperatures in the range of $0 - 1300^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ if couples are selected and calibrated and if attention is paid to details during design, fabrication, and installation."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 180, "line_start": 180, "page_hint": null, "section": "Temperature Measurement", "text": "Errors of $\\pm 8^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ under static and protected conditions may result if a"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 290, "line_start": 290, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "The data logger collects and stores information from up to 350 field-mounted instruments of all types."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 290, "line_start": 290, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "These instruments are scanned at 5-second intervals and selected groups of the numerical readings are automatically printed on log sheets in the appropriate engineering units once every hour, 4 hours, and 8 hours, or at any time, should the operator so request."}
{"claim_type": "table-reference", "line_end": 290, "line_start": 290, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "Out-of-limit alarms are actuated if any one of the 350 data points goes beyond acceptable values in either the high or low direction."}
{"claim_type": "reactor-physics", "line_end": 290, "line_start": 290, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "If the out-of-limit point or points are critical for good operation, the logger will scan a selected group of 64 data points continuously at a repetition rate of five times per second until the reactor system is again within its proper limits."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 317, "line_start": 317, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "By mid-year (FY-68) the HFIR control computer will be installed and the results of the preliminary control experiments will be available."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 325, "line_start": 325, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "These potential trouble areas are all in the analog signal handling part of the system and have to do with 1) noise rejection and filtering of the input signals, 2) analog input signal commutation, and 3) generation of analog output signals."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 325, "line_start": 325, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "For instance, an approximate cost to handle input signals on the MSRE computer is more than $100 per process variable."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 325, "line_start": 325, "page_hint": null, "section": "Computer Control and Data Logging", "text": "A conservative estimate of the number of signals to be brought into a computer on the MSBE would be 2000, which emphasizes the need for finding ways to reduce the input signal handling costs."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 335, "line_start": 335, "page_hint": null, "section": "Beryllium Monitoring", "text": "This instrument, at 1-1/2 minute intervals, automatically strikes an arc in a small bypass stream of air pumped from the stack and the light output is examined photoelectrically for the characteristic line produced by beryllium."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 383, "line_start": 383, "page_hint": null, "section": "Temperature Alarm Switches", "text": "For example, on-off limit switching in the MSRE is desirable over a $25^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ or less temperature increment at average temperatures of $1200^{\\circ}\\mathrm{F}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 383, "line_start": 383, "page_hint": null, "section": "Temperature Alarm Switches", "text": "This is only a $2\\%$ change and represents a severe challenge to existing methods."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 393, "line_start": 393, "page_hint": null, "section": "Process Radiation Monitoring", "text": "The materials of construction of the probe, however, limit the environmental temperature to approximately $70^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}$ for the sensor."}
